This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper focuses on privacy-preserving inference on standard, pre-trained models using encryption schemes, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper introduces a framework for neural network inference, which is a core topic in machine learning.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper evaluates the proposed framework on image classification tasks using the ImageNet dataset, which is a common benchmark in computer vision.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents several optimizations to improve the performance of the proposed framework, which involves algorithmic and data structure considerations.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a client-aided model using a two-party approach to compute activation functions, which involves system and control aspects.
